transcription.text:

Speaker 2: Yes, please, I'm going to, you guys sent me an order, but I did not order that.

Speaker 1: So I want to cancel it, please.

Speaker 2: Okay, what's your phone name and date of birth?

Speaker 1: My what? My phone number, you said?

Speaker 2: Your phone name and date of birth, please.

Speaker 1: My phone number, you said phone number, right? I'm sorry.

Speaker 2: No, your date of birth and your phone number.

Speaker 1: My date of birth, okay, my date of birth is April 1st, 1968.

Speaker 2: And your phone name?

Speaker 1: Diego Arboleda.

Speaker 2: Okay, sounds good.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so it looks like you do have a prescription with us for Viagra.

Speaker 2: It looks like you get a quantity of 10, 50 milligrams.

Speaker 1: So if you do not need any at the moment, Diego,

Speaker 2: then I can always go ahead and just pause your prescription.

Speaker 1: We can pause it for half a year, okay?

Speaker 2: All right, no problem. Thank you.

Speaker 1: Okay, well, you're all set. It's been paused. Have a good day. Bye.

Speaker 2: You too.
